
[1]putrefy

   PU'TREFY, v.t. [L. putrefacio; putris,putrid, and facio, to make.]

   1. To cause to dissolve; to disorganize and reduce to the simple
   constituent elements, as animal or vegetable bodies; to cause to rot.
   Heat and moisture soon putrefy dead flesh or vegetables.

   2. To corrupt; to make foul; as, to putrefy the air. [Little used.]

   3. To make morbid, carious or gangrenous; as, to putrefy an ulcer or
   wound.

       PU'TREFY, v.i. To dissolve and return to the original distinct
     elements, as animal and vegetable substances deprived of the living
                             principle; to rot.
